a is president chief executive officer director of the company effective may   mehrotra was a cofounder of sandisk and served as its president and ceo from  to  he drove the growth of the company from a startup in  to an industryleading fortune  company with revenues that reached  billion and ultimately culminated in a sale for  billion to western digital corporation in  his team pioneered a diversified and comprehensive portfolio of flash storage solutions that included removable products embedded mobile solutions client and enterprise solid state drives and innovative enterprise system solutions he also initiated and guided a highly successful year joint venture partnership with toshiba in nand flash memory technology development and manufacturing in addition he established and ran key manufacturing operations in china taiwan japan and malaysia ernest maddock mr ernest e maddock ia chief financial officer vice president  finance principal financial  accounting officer of micron technology inc from april  until he joined us mr maddock served as executive vice president and chief financial officer of riverbed technology from october  to april  mr maddock served as executive vice president and chief financial officer of lam research corporation after serving as lams vice president of global operations from october  to september  mr maddock currently serves as a member of the board of directors for intersil corporation mr maddock holds a bs in industrial management from the georgia institute of technology and an mba from georgia state university sumit sadana mr sumit sadana is executive vice president and chief business officer of the company he has  years of experience in the semiconductor industry including executive roles at ibm and freescale semiconductor and served most recently as executive vice president chief strategy officer and general manager enterprise solutions at sandisk the new integrated business and strategy organization aims to provide an agile struc